George TALNICOFF v. Walter A. HUNTER, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 3716. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 22, 1948. Kenneth L. Smith, of Denver, Colo., for appellant. Randolph Carpenter, U. S. Atty., and Eugene W. Davis, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and BRATTON and HUXMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on ground that notice of appeal not filed within time.
